..
Here’s a professional email template you can use:


---

Subject: Reminder: Planned Leave for [Festival Name]

Dear [Manager's Name],

I hope you are doing well. This is a gentle reminder about my planned leave from [start date] to [end date], which I had applied for earlier to celebrate [festival name] and travel home.

I will ensure all my tasks are completed or handed over before my leave to avoid any disruptions during my absence. Please feel free to let me know if there’s anything else you need me to address.

Thank you for your support and understanding.

Best regards,
[Your Name]


---

Let me know if you’d like any further modifications!




work from home template 

Here’s a professional email template to request an exception for work from home:


---

Subject: Request for Exception: Work from Home for 2 Days

Dear [Manager's Name],

I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to request an exception to work from home for two days, [specific dates], as I have traveled to my hometown due to [reason, e.g., personal/family reasons].

I assure you that I will remain fully available during working hours and will ensure that all my tasks and responsibilities are managed without any disruption.

I kindly request your approval for this exception, and please let me know if there is anything further you need from my side.

Thank you for your understanding and consideration.

Best regards,
[Your Name]


---

Feel free to adjust the details as needed!
